main event: A civilian observer reported seeing 35 dim masses of light that appeared to hover in formation, resembling birds, in Cloverdale, California on April 6, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 20 minutes,The formation of lights was moving in a northward direction,The observer noted bright calm moonlight during the sighting,The sighting was reported to the Air Force after a similar report on April 23, 1966,The report contained communication from the U.S. Air Force thanking the witness for the UFO sighting report.
sighted object: dim masses of light in formation
witness description: A civilian observer who had never seen anything unusual in the sky before.
